The paper discusses a security vulnerability in the GSM mobile telephony system and proposes a modification to enhance authentication without changing the existing infrastructure. This suggests that the paper belongs to the computer security (cs.CR) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the proposed modification involves changes to the authentication centers and SIMs, indicating that the paper may also belong to the software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the transparency properties of the proposed enhancement, which suggests that it may also belong to the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category.
